The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Chelsea seal second spot
London, May 8 (Reuters): Ten-man Chelsea held out for a 1-1 draw at Manchester United on Saturday to seal second place in the Premier League and a guaranteed slot in next seasons Champions League. Chelsea were cruising after Jesper Gronkjaer scored in the 19th minute and keeper Carlo Cudicini brilliantly saved a penalty from Uniteds Ruud Van Nistelrooy just before halftime. But a 73rd minute red card for Chelsea defender Robert Huth was followed four minutes later by a goalkeeping howler from Cudicini which handed Van Nistelrooy an easy equaliser. Bremen champions Meanwhile, Werder Bremen sealed their fourth Bundesliga title with a stylish 3-1 victory over second-placed Bayern Munich on Saturday.  Copyright 
